Ate here last night.  It was a little out of the way so we walked by it at first.  We were able to get a table outside even though we didn't have a reservation.  We had a shrimp appetizer which was very tasty along with 2 tapas; foie gras and grilled vegetables.  Both were quite enjoyable.  Then came the seafood paella which was great.  We each had a couple of glasses of the house wine and finished it off with chocolate cake with vanilla ice cream.  It was a great meal.
